<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1006" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 703.3212/18.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Consul Silliman, from Teoloyucan, August 13, asks me to telegraph
                            following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>To the Brazilian Minister solely is due the preparation of the
                                    document which was signed this afternoon terminating the civil
                                    war in Mexico.</p>
                                <p rend="right">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>It is also proper for the Department to know how great a source of help
                            and strength the Brazilian Minister has been to our Consuls in
                            Mexico.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>